The paper focuses on recognizing personality traits from videos using various modalities such as face, environment, audio, and transcription features. This involves using deep convolutional neural networks for feature extraction and Long Short-Term Memory networks for integrating temporal information. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also involves affective computing and natural language processing, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper also involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
